### Data Flow

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["CLLocationManager<br/>(Native Swift)"] -->|"MethodChannel +<br/>EventChannel"| B["LocationService<br/>(Dart)"]
    B -->|"Reverse geocode"| C["geocoding<br/>package"]
    B -->|"Categorize +<br/>Generate prompts"| D["today_screen.dart"]
    D -->|"Render chips"| E["User sees<br/>location prompts"]
    F["Settings toggle"] -->|"SharedPrefs"| D
```

### Dynamic Prompt Engine

The prompt engine generates **contextual questions** based on:
- **Place category** (13 categories: restaurant, café, park, gym, office, school, etc.)
- **Time of day** (early morning → night)
- **Duration** (quick stop → most of the day)
- **Visit frequency** (3+ visits triggers "what keeps you coming back?")
- **Multi-place visits** ("Busy day visiting X, Y, Z — what was the highlight?")

Prompts are generated for both **"What went well?"** and **"What was challenging?"** fields.

---

## Proposed Changes

**No code changes needed.** The audit confirms the feature is fully implemented and wired end-to-end.

> [!NOTE]
> The Android side currently has location permissions declared but no native plugin for Fused Location Provider. The Dart [LocationService](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/location_service.dart#247-1005) uses platform channels that will gracefully fail on Android (caught by `try/catch`). If you need Android native support in the future, a `CoreLocationPlugin` equivalent in Kotlin would need to be written.

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (iOS Device)

Since there are no existing automated tests in this project, verification must be done on-device:

1. **Build and run** on your physical iPhone:
   ```
   flutter run
   ```

2. **First launch (opt-out behavior)**:
   - Open the app → you should see a location permission prompt (since the feature is **enabled by default**)
   - Grant "While Using App" permission
   - Navigate to the Today screen → after ~2 seconds, location-based suggestion chips should appear under "What went well?" and "What was challenging?"

3. **Verify dynamic prompts**:
   - The chips should show prompts mentioning your current location name
   - Tapping a chip should insert the prompt text into the journal field

4. **Settings toggle (opt-out)**:
   - Go to Settings → find "Location Suggestions" under Preferences
   - Toggle **OFF** → cached location data should be cleared
   - Go back to Today screen → no location chips should appear
   - Toggle back **ON** → permission should be re-requested, chips should appear again after granting

5. **Verify console logs**:
   - In the terminal running `flutter run`, look for `📍` prefixed debug prints showing region enter/exit events
